    "created_at": "2011-09-07T20:41:31Z",
    "updated_at": "2011-09-07T20:41:31Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In these, stdin.encoding is None, and pretty much all of our decoding uses `enc=sys.stdin.encoding or sys.getdefaultencoding()`, which will return ASCII, so any unicode characters get clobbered.\n\nIf we change these cases to `sys.stdin.encoding or locale.getpreferredencoding() or sys.getdefaultencoding()`, then we should get more sensible, less conservative behavior.\n"
  },
